an, R., Safriel, U.N., Noy-Meir, I., Schiller, G., Spatiotemporal variation in seed dispersal and recruitment near and far from Pinus halepensis (2000) Ecology, 81, pp. 2156-2169; Neyman, J., Scott, E., Statistical approach to the problems of cosmology (1958) Journal of the Royal Statistical Society, Series B, 20, pp. 1-43; Nieppola, J., Long-term vegetation changes in stands of Pinus sylvestris in southern Finland (1992) Journal of Vegetation Science, 3, pp. 475-484; Oliver, C.D., Larson, B.C., (1990) Forest Stand Dynamics., , McGraw-Hill, New York; Ortega Villazán, M.T., (1992) El Clima del Sector Norte de la Cordillera Ibérica: Estudio Geográfico de la Sierra de la Demanda a la del Moncayo., , Junta de Castilla y León, Valladolid, Spain; Payette, S., Filion, L., White spruce expansion at the tree line and recent climatic change (1985) Canadian Journal of Forest Research, 15, pp. 241-251; Pélissier, R., Goreaud, F., A practical approach to the study of spatial structure in simple cases of heterogeneous vegetation (2001) Journal of Vegetation Science, 12, pp. 99-108; Peltzer, D.A., Köchy, M., Competitive effects of grasses and woody plants in mixed-grass prairie (2001) Journal of Ecology, 89, pp. 519-527; Peñalba, M.C., The history of the Holocene vegetation in northern Spain from pollen analysis (1994) Journal of Ecology, 82, pp. 815-832; Van Der Pijl, L., (1982) Principles of Dispersal in Higher Plants., , Springer-Verlag, Berlin; Portnoy, S., Willson, M.F., Seed dispersal curves: Behavior of the tail of the distribution (1993) Evolutionary Ecology, 7, pp. 25-44; Ribbens, E., Silander, J.A., Pacala, S.W., Seedling recruitment in forests: Calibrating models to predict patterns of tree seedling dispersion (1994) Ecology, 75, pp. 1794-1806; Richardson, D.M., Bond, W.J., Determinants of plant distribution: Evidence from pine invasions (1991) American Naturalist, 137, pp. 639-668; Ripley, B.D., Modelling spatial patterns (1977) Journal of the Royal Statistical Society